description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Night Carer 59773 CHPE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Foxwood, Norwich&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;£13,335 to £13,602 per annum&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;25.55 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Permanent contract&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Foxwood is a short break residential home based in Sprowston in Norwich. We provide short breaks for children with learning/physical disabilities including young people with complex health needs and challenging behaviours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a caring and compassionate individual to join our established night team to provide a safe and secure environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a skilled and/or experienced individual with knowledge of working with children with diverse range of individual needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will provide and ensure that young people receive a high standard of care during the night with support from a senior staff member.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally you should hold an NVQ level 3 for young people or Diploma CWDC level 3 or willingness to undertake this qualification.  You will be provided with regular supervision and training to assist with your job role and your development. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is nights however you will be expected to work some days attending meetings and training.&lt;/p&gt;
